  Sashnov Alexander's homepage
  
In the past it was a Makefile which converts .m4 files directly to .html
But since 2016 hosting at http://sashnov.nm.ru/ was closed and I decide
to move my page to pages.github.com  The service uses Jekyll for server-
side generation of .html files out of .md (MarkDown) files.

It seemed easy to convert my .m4 files to .md so I have a go.
It is hard to install the latest version of Jekyll so I use
the official docker container jekyll/jekyll.

  Getting started

https://help.github.com/articles/using-jekyll-as-a-static-site-generator-with-github-pages/
https://help.github.com/categories/github-pages-basics/
https://help.github.com/articles/further-reading-on-github-pages/
https://pages.github.com/ - GitHub Pages tutorial

$ sudo apt-get install docker.io
$ docker pull jekyll/jekyll:pages
$ make serve



