Jekyll’s rules
    Any file in the source directory is copied directly into the site directory.
    Unless the file that has a YAML header. These files can make use of the Liquid templating language.
    Unless the file is in _posts. These files build up a data object representing all of your site’s content that can be referenced when templating.
    Posts can specify a permalink to generate a page at a different location than where the post resides in the source directory.
